value.title: Biden's Keystone XL pipeline cancellation is gut punch to small businesses
value.excerpt: While opponents of the long-controversial Keystone XL Pipeline cheered its cancellation by President Biden's administration, others like Nebraska truck driver Chris Olsen shook their heads in dismay.

value.title: Biden administration designates Myanmar military takeover as a coup
value.excerpt: The Biden administration has formally determined that the military takeover in Myanmar constitutes a coup d'état, a designation that requires the US to cut its foreign assistance to the country.

value.title: Angel dad rips Biden's immigration policies: 'I don't know how they can justify it'
value.excerpt: A man whose son was killed by an illegal immigrant is very upset with President Biden's immigration policies.

value.title: DOJ asks Supreme Court to cancel arguments over Trump border wall and 'remain in Mexico' policy
value.excerpt: The Justice Department asked the Supreme Court Monday to cancel courtroom arguments scheduled for later this month over two aspects of Donald Trump's immigration policy, a reflection of the new administration's reversal on both issues.

value.title: New DOJ hire is former colleague of Hunter Biden defense attorney
value.excerpt: The newly selected acting head of the Justice Department's criminal division is a former colleague of the attorney now representing Hunter Biden in the face of a DOJ investigation.

value.title: Live Updates: Impeachment Managers Call Trump ‘Singularly Responsible’ for Riot
value.excerpt: The nine House impeachment managers presented their case against former President Donald J. Trump in a filing. Mr. Trump has a noon deadline to outline his defense. President Biden will sign executive orders on immigration.

value.title: When will Biden ask SCOTUS to uphold Obamacare?
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has been in office for less than two weeks, but a looming question is when, not whether, his Justice Department will change the federal government's position before the Supreme Court on the Affordable Care Act.

value.title: Trump's Oval Office meeting with 4 election conspiracists spiraled into a chaotic multi-hour screaming match
value.excerpt: "Are you out of your f---ing mind?," White House advisor Eric Herschmann told conspiracy-wielding layer Sidney Powell at one point, Axios reported.

value.title: Live Updates: Biden meets with Republican senators on coronavirus aid
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Monday night said that he's unwilling to settle on an insufficient coronavirus aid package.

value.title: Trump campaign's post-election legal spending topped $7M, with Kasowitz in the lead
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign paid law firms and other legal providers more than $7 million from Nov. 4 through the end of last year, a Reuters analysis of Federal Election Commission records shows.

value.title: MyPillow Twitter account permanently suspended following Trump ally, CEO Mike Lindell's ban from platform
value.excerpt: Twitter has suspended the MyPillow account after banning CEO Mike Lindell's account for perpetuating claims that Trump won the presidential election.

value.title: Ex-NFL star Marcellus Wiley calls for 'separate transgender category' in school sports after Biden order
value.excerpt: Former NFL star and current Fox Sports 1 host Marcellus Wiley called last week for the creation of a "separate transgender category" for youth athletics.

value.title: Biden hosts GOP senators as part of Covid-19 stimulus outreach
value.excerpt: White House spokeswoman Jen Psaki defended the size of the administration's $1.9 trillion Covid-19 relief proposal, calling it "incredibly urgent" ahead of a meeting with Republican senators on Monday.

value.title: Biden administration cites climate change as a 'racial justice issue'
value.excerpt: Climate Adviser Gina McCarthy explained that challenges are exacerbated in communities that haven't been invested in.

value.title: Howard Kurtz: Media will use impeachment trial to ‘convict Donald Trump in the court of public opinion’
value.excerpt: Fox News media analyst Howard Kurtz predicts Donald Trump’s second impeachment trial will be “grand political theater” that will dominate media coverage.

value.title: Biden State Dept. spokeswoman called police 'largest threat to US national security': Report
value.excerpt: Jalina Porter, who has been named deputy spokesperson for the U.S. State Department under President Biden, wrote that U.S. cops posed the largest national security threat because of attacks against Blacks

value.title: Ukraine's Zelensky 'offended' by media reporting that Trump 'put pressure' on him
value.excerpt: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signaled that he was more upset about the aftermath of his now-infamous July 2019 phone call with then-President Donald Trump than the actual call.

value.title: Trump residency at Mar-a-Lago under Palm Beach legal review
value.excerpt: Palm Beach, Fla., officials are conducting a legal review into former President Donald Trump's residency at Mar-a-Lago, Fox News confirmed Monday.

value.title: White House reached out to Manchin after Harris' West Virginia interview
value.excerpt: The White House called Democratic Sen. Joe Manchin after Vice President Kamala Harris conducted interviews with West Virginia media, according to a person with knowledge of the conversation.

value.title: Joe Biden Threatens Sanctions Following Myanmar Coup, Says U.S. Will 'Stand Up For Democracy'
value.excerpt: "In a democracy, force should never seek to overrule the will of the people or attempt to erase the outcome of a credible election," the president said in his first statement on the issue.

value.title: David Schoen: What to know about Trump impeachment defense attorney
value.excerpt: High-profile civil rights attorney David Schoen, who before Jeffrey Epstein's death was in discussions to join his legal team, will be one of the two top members of former President Donald Trump's legal team for his impeachment trial, which is set to start in earnest in the Senate next week.

value.title: Kudlow: Trump was 'consequential, brilliant' president on policy
value.excerpt: New Fox Business host Larry Kudlow said Monday that former President Donald Trump would go down as a "brilliant, consequential" president on policy terms and would have been better served to focus on his achievements instead of fighting the election result in the final weeks of his term.

value.title: The Daily 202: Kinzinger says Republicans need ‘an intervention’ to kick Trump habit
value.excerpt: We’ve got to reject the dark conspiracy theories and lies," said the Illinois Republican, who is starting a PAC to break Donald Trump's stranglehold on the GOP.

value.title: Kinzinger launches new PAC to 'take back' GOP from Trump
value.excerpt: Under fire by many in his own party for his vote to impeach then-President Trump, Republican Rep. Adam Kinzinger of Illinois is fighting to "take back" the GOP.

value.title: Biden and Harris to meet Republican senators to push for Covid aid package – live updates
